[stdout] [0m[49m[39m   40,  40[0m:[39m[49m ## Reproduced Failure
[0m[49m[39m   41,  41[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   42,  42[0m:[39m[49m The `repro/` project contains `LuceneLinkageErrorReproTest`, which:
[0m[49m[39m   43,  43[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   44,  44[0m:[39m[49m - Creates two sequential `URLClassLoader` instances loading `lucene-core-4.10.2.jar`
[0m[49m[39m   45,  45[0m:[39m[49m - Calls `AttributeSource.addAttribute(CharTermAttribute.class)` through each loader
[0m[49m[39m   46,  46[0m:[39m[49m - Asserts that the second call throws `LinkageError`
[0m[49m[39m   47,  47[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   48,  48[0m:[39m[49m On Java 21 the test **fails** (BUILD FAILURE) because the `LinkageError` is no longer thrown — the JVM fixed the constraint. This is the correct red state: the test documents the Java 8 bug by asserting the broken behavior.
[0m[49m[39m   49,  49[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   50,  50[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m   51,  51[0m:[39m[49m [ERROR] LuceneLinkageErrorReproTest.secondDeployThrowsLinkageError
[0m[49m[39m   52,  52[0m:[39m[49m   Expected LinkageError on second deploy (Java 8 behavior).
[0m[49m[39m   53,  53[0m:[39m[49m   Running on Java 21 which has fixed this JVM loader constraint issue.
[0m[49m[39m   54,  54[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m   55,  55[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   56,  56[0m:[39m[49m ---
[0m[49m[39m   57,  57[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   58,  58[0m:[39m[49m ## Root Cause
[0m[49m[39m   59,  59[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   60,  60[0m:[39m[49m Lucene 4.x's `AttributeFactory$1` uses `MethodHandle.invokeExact()` with a typed return descriptor:
[0m[49m[39m   61,  61[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   62,  62[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m   63,  63[0m:[39m[49m invokevirtual #3  // MethodHandle.invokeExact:()Lorg/apache/lucene/util/AttributeImpl;
[0m[49m[39m   64,  64[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m   65,  65[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   66,  66[0m:[39m[49m The JVM's loader-constraint mechanism records: for the classloader of `AttributeFactory$1`, the class `AttributeImpl` in this descriptor must be the same object as the `AttributeImpl` seen by the bootstrap classloader's `MethodHandle`.
[0m[49m[39m   67,  67[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   68,  68[0m:[39m[49m **First deploy (WebappClassLoader A):** constraint recorded — `AttributeImpl` = A's class object.  
[0m[49m[39m   69,  69[0m:[39m[49m **Second deploy (WebappClassLoader B, same JVM):** B loads a new `AttributeImpl` class object. The JVM detects B's `AttributeImpl` ≠ A's `AttributeImpl` and throws:
[0m[49m[39m   70,  70[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   71,  71[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m   72,  72[0m:[39m[49m java.lang.LinkageError: loader constraint violation: when resolving method
[0m[49m[39m   73,  73[0m:[39m[49m "java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle.invokeExact()Lorg/apache/lucene/util/AttributeImpl;"
[0m[49m[39m   74,  74[0m:[39m[49m the class loader (instance of org/apache/catalina/loader/WebappClassLoader) of the
[0m[49m[39m   75,  75[0m:[39m[49m current class, org/apache/lucene/util/AttributeFactory$1, and the class loader
[0m[49m[39m   76,  76[0m:[39m[49m (instance of <bootloader>) for resolved class, java/lang/invoke/MethodHandle,
[0m[49m[39m   77,  77[0m:[39m[49m have different Class objects for the type org/apache/lucene/util/AttributeImpl;
[0m[49m[39m   78,  78[0m:[39m[49m used in the signature
[0m[49m[39m   79,  79[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m   80,  80[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   81,  81[0m:[39m[49m This is a Java 8 JVM defect in loader-constraint tracking for `MethodHandle` invocations. It was fixed in Java 9 (JDK-8072008 / JDK-8130305).
[0m[49m[39m   82,  82[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   83,  83[0m:[39m[49m ---
[0m[49m[39m   84,  84[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   85,  85[0m:[39m[49m ## Fix
[0m[49m[39m   86,  86[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   87,  87[0m:[39m[49m **Primary fix: upgrade to Java 11+.**
[0m[49m[39m   88,  88[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   89,  89[0m:[39m[49m On Java 11+ the JVM no longer records the stale loader constraint, so a second `URLClassLoader` loading the same Lucene jar succeeds without error.
[0m[49m[39m   90,  90[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   91,  91[0m:[39m[49m **Application-level workarounds (for users stuck on Java 8):**
[0m[49m[39m   92,  92[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   93,  93[0m:[39m[49m 1. Move `lucene-core.jar` to Tomcat's `shared/lib` directory so it is loaded by the shared classloader, not the `WebappClassLoader`. Only one `AttributeImpl` class object ever exists.
[0m[49m[39m   94,  94[0m:[39m[49m 2. Avoid hot redeploys; restart the JVM between deploys.
[0m[49m[39m   95,  95[0m:[39m[49m 3. Upgrade to Lucene 5+, which replaced the `MethodHandle`-based `AttributeFactory` with a plain reflective approach.
[0m[49m[39m   96,  96[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   97,  97[0m:[39m[49m ---
[0m[49m[39m   98,  98[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m   99,  99[0m:[39m[49m ## Repaired Project
[0m[49m[39m  100, 100[0m:[39m[49m 
